Vice President Kamala Harris held a virtual meeting with faith leaders in her official reception room, expressing her gratitude for their support and guidance. She acknowledged the challenging times brought on by the pandemic and commended the faith leaders for their unwavering strength and service to their communities. Harris discussed the administration's efforts, such as the American Rescue Plan and vaccination distribution, to bring hope and relief to the American people. She also addressed issues like hate crimes, immigration, and voting rights, seeking input and collaboration from the faith leaders. The Vice President emphasized the importance of faith and community in overcoming challenges and building a better future.